==Awards and honors==
Chenoweth was awarded an honorary doctorate in Performing Arts from the [[University of North Carolina School of the Arts]] in 2009, where she was the commencement speaker.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20110211073223/http://uncsa.edu/pressreleases/Releases2009/May09/COMMENCEMENTSPEAKERS09.htm "Film, TV and Broadway Star Kristin Chenoweth to Deliver University Commencement Address at UNCSA"], [[University of North Carolina School of the Arts]] press release, May 22, 2009, accessed March 7, 2010.</ref> Oklahoma City University, where she received her undergraduate and master's degrees, awarded her an honorary [[Doctor of Humane Letters]] degree in 2013.<ref name=Allen/> In 2010, Chenoweth was inducted into the [[Oklahoma Hall of Fame]].<ref>[http://www.oklahomahof.com/HallofFame/SearchbyName.aspx "Search by Name"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150503012512/http://www.oklahomahof.com/HallofFame/SearchbyName.aspx |date=May 3, 2015 }}, Oklahoma Hall of Fame, accessed February 28, 2015</ref> In 2011, she won the [[GLAAD Vanguard Award]].<ref>Donnelly, Matt. [http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/gossip/2011/04/glaad-media-awards-kristen-chenoweth-dolly-parton.html "Kristin Chenoweth, Dolly Parton rally for GLAAD Media Awards in L.A."], ''Los Angeles Times'' blogs, April 11, 2011, accessed April 9, 2012</ref>

In 2012, the Broken Arrow Performing Arts Center named its theatre the Kristin Chenoweth Theatre.<ref>[http://www.thepacba.com/kristin.html "The Kristin Chenoweth Theatre"], Broken Arrow Performing Arts Center, accessed December 1, 2014</ref> Chenoweth received a star on the [[Hollywood Walk of Fame]] in 2015.<ref name=HollywoodWalk>Adams, Thelma. [https://variety.com/2015/tv/spotlight/kristin-chenoweth-walk-of-fame-watch-1201547803/ "Kristin Chenoweth Receives a Star on the Hollywood Walk of Fame"], ''Variety'', July 24, 2015</ref> In 2015, she was inducted as an honorary member of the [[Sigma Alpha Iota]] music fraternity's Sigma Theta chapter at [[Eastman School of Music]].<ref>[https://www.facebook.com/SAISigmaTheta/photos/a.565449483572193.1073741834.461842480599561/851004528350019/?type=3&theater Kristen Chenowth], [[Sigma Alpha Iota]] of the Sigma Theta chapter, [[Eastman School of Music]], October 10, 2015</ref>

